## Limitations
The primary limitation of this report is the reliance on secondary sources, which may present interpretations rather than primary historical evidence. Additionally, the complexity of defining racism and its historical manifestations means that conclusions may vary significantly among scholars. The report also does not cover all possible perspectives, particularly those from non-Western contexts, which may offer different insights into the origins of racism.